Three Die in 140-Vehicle Expressway Pileup
BEIJING , February 26 ( Xinhua ) -- Three people were killed and at least six were injured in a traffic accident on the Langfang Section of the Beijing-Tianjin Expressway today .
An official of the Traffic Control Department of Longfang City , Hebei Province , said that the accident involved 140 motor vehicles in a chain collision .
He said that the accident occurred at eight o ' clock this morning , and its direct cause was heavy fog .
The accident caused a traffic jam on a 12-kilometer long lane .
However , he said , traffic on the expressway was not halted , and all the damaged cars had been removed from the expressway by noon .
